## üõ†Ô∏è How to Contribute

### 1. Open an Issue
- Spot a bug? Want to propose a feature? Start by opening an [Issue](https://github.com/TheThirdRoom/canary/issues).
- Clearly describe the problem or idea.
- If you're planning to submit code, mention that in the issue.

### 2. Fork and Clone
```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/canary.git
cd canary

3. Set Up Locally
	‚Ä¢	Follow the instructions in README.md to install dependencies and run the project locally.

4. Create a New Branch
git checkout -b your-feature-name

5. Make Changes
	‚Ä¢	Follow existing code style and structure.
	‚Ä¢	Add tests or documentation where relevant.

6. Commit and Push
git commit -m "Brief description of your changes"
git push origin your-feature-name

7. Open a Pull Request
	‚Ä¢	Go to the original repo: https://github.com/TheThirdRoom/canary
	‚Ä¢	Click ‚ÄúCompare & pull request‚Äù
	‚Ä¢	Explain your changes and link to the related issue.

